"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-04-14-jamaica-three-men-paris-olympics-discus-throw-stonas-pb\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Jamaica will have three representatives in the men's discus throw at a second consecutive Olympic Games after Roje Stona achieved the qualifying mark on Sunday when he finished second at the Oklahoma Throws Series World Invitational with a personal best 69.05m.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9983676105408126, \"rank\": 0.0014158827529071499, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three representatives\", \"from\": 18, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's discus throw\", \"from\": 43, \"to\": 65}, {\"ngram\": \"a second consecutive Olympic Games\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"Roje Stona\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"the qualifying mark\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 149}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 159}, {\"ngram\": \"the Oklahoma Throws Series World Invitational\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 232}, {\"ngram\": \"a personal best 69.05m.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 261}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stona improved on his previous personal best 68.64m set in May last year that qualified him for the World Championships in Budapest, Hungary and joins Ralford Mullings (69.89m) and Traves Smikle (67.83m) as Jamaican men who have gone over the automatic qualifying distance of 67.20m for the Paris Olympics this summer.\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9992752663540198, \"rank\": 0.0007240800332443102, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource